				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2020 19:55:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MadEngineer</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5702200</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A sticking point for me was the 5903-OUT nomenclature: I didn't see an explanation for why a Foundation researcher would come up with that term for the affected people, rather than just 5903-1 or something like that. The result was that it looked grafted on to make the &quot;out-group&quot; reference. Maybe say something about the final result being a mirror image of the original person, and thus being &quot;reflected out&quot; through the plane of symmetry?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
